questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pretoria.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Afric&lt;/strong&gt;a is the southernmost country on the African continent.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;South Africa has three capital cities namely,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Pretoria,&amp;nbsp;Bloemfontein,&amp;nbsp;Cape Town.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pretoria is the&amp;nbsp;administrative&amp;nbsp;capital of South Africa.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Pretoria is host to &lt;strong&gt;all foreign embassies to South Africa.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Pretoria was founded in 1855 by &lt;strong&gt;Marthinus Pretorius.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The city&amp;nbsp;Pretoria is named after the Voortrekker leader&lt;strong&gt; Andries Pretorius.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Pretoria is popularly called &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Jacaranda City&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; due to the large number of&amp;nbsp;jacaranda trees planted along its streets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;South Africa became Republic on&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;31 May 1961.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Durban&lt;/strong&gt; is a coastal city in South Africa known for its African, Indian and colonial influences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bloemfontein&lt;/strong&gt; is the judicial capital of South Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cape Town&lt;/strong&gt; is the legislative capital of South Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mihir&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Sen&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mihir&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Sen&lt;/strong&gt; was the&lt;strong&gt; first Indian swimmer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to swim the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;English&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;channel&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is the only man to swim oceans of five continents in 1958.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was awarded&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Padma&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Shri&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Padma&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Bhusan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arati&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Saha&lt;/strong&gt; was the&lt;strong&gt; first Indian woman&lt;/strong&gt; to swim across the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;English&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Channel&lt;/strong&gt; in 1959.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;She was also the first female &lt;strong&gt;sportsperson&lt;/strong&gt; to win the &lt;strong&gt;Padma&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Shri&lt;/strong&gt; in 1960.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Abhinav Bindra&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is&amp;nbsp;a distinguished player in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;shooting&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;games.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Abhinav Bindra made history in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Beijing 2008&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Olympics&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;by becoming the first Indian to win an individual gold medal.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first Indian&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to have held concurrently the world and Olympic titles for the men&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;10-meter air rifle event,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;having earned those honours at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;2008 Summer Olympics&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Milkha Singh&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Milkha Singh is also&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;known as the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Flying Sikh.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indian&amp;nbsp;track-and-field athlete&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;who became the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first&amp;nbsp;Indian&amp;nbsp;male to reach the final of an Olympic athletics&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;event when he placed fourth in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;400-meter race at the 1960 Olympic Games in Rome.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Major Dhyanchand&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was an&lt;strong&gt; Indian Hockey player &lt;/strong&gt;who is also known as &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;The Wizard of Hockey&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; for his extraordinary goal-scoring feats.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was a three-time &lt;strong&gt;gold medalist &lt;/strong&gt;for hockey in &lt;strong&gt;Olympic 1928, 1932 and 1936&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Dhyanchand Award also known as the Dhyan Chand Award for Lifetime Achievement in Sports and Games is awarded in his honour.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first Common Wealth Games was held in the year 1930.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Earlier the game was known as the British Empire Games.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was held in 1930 in Hamilton, Ontario.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Since then it held at every fourth year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The next Commonwealth Games would be held in Birmingham from 27 July to 7 August 2022.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Group of Monuments at Mahabalipuran one of the &amp;quot;UNESCO World Heritage Site&amp;quot; founded by the Pallava kings is in _______ district of _______.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. Kancheepuram, Tamil Nadu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. Sivagangai, Tamil Nadu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. Siligiris, Tamil Nadu&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Group of Monuments at &lt;strong&gt;Mahabalipuram&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;one of the &amp;quot;UNESCO World Heritage Site&amp;quot; founded by the &lt;strong&gt;Pallava kings&lt;/strong&gt; is in &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kancheepuram&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; district of &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_2840C&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;It lies on the &lt;strong&gt;Coromandel Coast.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;It is believed to have been built in the &lt;strong&gt;7th and 8th centuries.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;There are temples in the shape of chariots, cave sanctuaries, giant open air reliefs, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The most famous are the five&amp;nbsp;monolithic structures known as &lt;strong&gt;Five Rathas&lt;/strong&gt;.There are believed to be the structure of five pandavas. These Ratha temples are constructed on the style of the Buddhist viharas and chaityas. The unfinished three-storey Dharmaraja Ratha is the largest.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;However, the temples are believed to be dedicated to deities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The site has been managed by the Archaeological Survey of India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ernst Mayr.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ernst Mayr&lt;/strong&gt; established &lt;strong&gt;evolutionary biology as a separate field of research&lt;/strong&gt; in the United States which &lt;strong&gt;earned &lt;/strong&gt;him the name&lt;strong&gt; &amp;ldquo;Darwin of the 20th century.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ernst Mayr &lt;/strong&gt;from &lt;strong&gt;Germany&lt;/strong&gt; helped to define&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the modern synthesis of evolutionary theory.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Har Gobind Khorana&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&lt;strong&gt; Marshall Warren Nirenberg&lt;/strong&gt; were&amp;nbsp;Biochemists who received the &lt;strong&gt;Nobel Prize in&amp;nbsp;Physiology in 1968 &lt;/strong&gt;for &lt;strong&gt;decoding the genetic material of DNA.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Katherine Esau&lt;/strong&gt; was a &lt;strong&gt;German-American botanist &lt;/strong&gt;who received the &lt;strong&gt;National Medal of Science for her work on plant anatomy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
